From: Mono OpenWrt <mono-openwrt@local>
Subject: selinux-policy: let wg re-open netifd's config pipe

netifd's wireguard proto handler builds the tunnel config in memory and
pipes it into `wg syncconf <iface> /dev/stdin`. wg does not read the
inherited fd directly: fopen("/dev/stdin") re-opens the pipe through
/proc/self/fd/0, and with the open_perms policy capability active that
requires `open` on netifd's fifo, which the inherited read/write grant
from the agent template does not include. The sync therefore fails
unconditionally with EACCES while enforcing, and netifd loops the
interface in pending/retry forever. The failure is silent because kernel
auditing is off by default, so no AVC ever reaches the log.

Grant the missing `open`, mirroring the explicit ucode fifo open added
for the same reason in the bring-up patch.

--- a/src/agent/sysagent/wireguardtoolssysagent.cil
+++ b/src/agent/sysagent/wireguardtoolssysagent.cil
@@ -42,6 +42,11 @@
 
       (call .ucode.readwriteinherited_subj_fifo_files (subj))
       (allow subj .ucode.subj (fifo_file (open)))
+
+      ;; netifd's wireguard proto script pipes the config into
+      ;; `wg syncconf <iface> /dev/stdin`; reopening the inherited pipe
+      ;; via /proc/self/fd/0 requires open on top of inherited read/write
+      (allow subj .netif.server.subj (fifo_file (open)))
 
       (call wireguard.tmp.list_file_dirs (subj))
       (call wireguard.tmp.readwrite_file_files (subj))))
